reviews.title: Just a little more attention to the Customer
reviews.text: Nice ambiance, good food. One tip for the person who brings the guests to the reserved spot: ask if the table provided also meets the wish. We were placed at a high table with 'bar stool' and we don't like that. Before we could even say anything, the employee had already turned around and disappeared. These (customer-friendliness and attentiveness) are just the little things that allow the restaurant to stand out from the rest. Furthermore, had a nice evening

reviews.title: It was another typical Thursday 😂🤩
reviews.text:
Good food. Good food. Were not at the place we had asked for (at the bar) while there was enough space. 

The tendency is to serve quickly. We had a small sandwich beforehand with a dish of delicious patanegra. Great! An appetizer in itself. 
It would be really nice if then, after clearing, your starter is not there within 3 minutes. 

Indicated that we wish for more time after the starter. This was picked up well. But it's a pity staff don't see this for themselves. 

Dessert, cheese board, was put down (in the wrong order) and the names of the cheeses in question are not known. Tastes delicious, by the way!  
Quality was fine, good food! Temperature in the dining room was blissful (also important). 

With a little more emphasis on ‘creating a pleasant evening for the Customer’ it would have been an excellent one. 

We will definitely be back.

reviews.title: Delicious food in an atmospheric atmosphere

reviews.title: Dinner on Monday

reviews.title: Disappointing

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

articleContent.title: Your family-friendly guide to Greenville, SC

seoInfo.metaDescription: Picnics, waterparks, museums, festivals, and plenty of unexpected all-ages activities—the equation for the perfect family getaway can be tough to balance. But there’s one place that does just this, promising plenty of memories to pack along with the souvenirs. Greenville, South Carolina checks all of the boxes, from hotels with plenty of family-friendly amenities to museums with interactive exhibits that’ll hold everyone’s attention (even a rambunctious toddler). Those in charge of packing can breathe easy: the weather is great year-round—the hottest month is July with temps up to 89 degrees, and the coolest is January, when the high hits around 55 degrees.
Make every meal an adventure in Türkiye, with standout dishes that tell a thousand tales

articleContent.title: The best outdoor activity in every US state

seoInfo.metaDescription: America is a vast nation that offers every type of activity you can imagine. Here are the best outdoor activity in every state.

I’ve always loved train travel. There’s something special about settling into a window seat and watching the landscape drift past. And as a wheelchair user, that joy only grows when the journey feels easy: level boarding, space to move, and the kind of accessibility that lets you fully relax. For me, the best train rides—like weaving through the Tuscan countryside on Trenitalia—are never just a way to get from A to B; they're part of the adventure.

articleContent.title: Why Greenville, SC is the perfect mix of adventure and luxury

seoInfo.metaDescription: There are few places that blend luxury and outdoor adventure like Greenville, South Carolina. The days (and mild weather) are made for adrenaline rushes of all types, while the region’s spas, fine dining, and boutique properties serve up luxury experiences that last well into the evening. It’s not hard to dive into a handful of the many treats on offer, and crafting an itinerary that incorporates a little bit of everything is how you’ll find yourself with a Greenville-shaped spot forever in your heart.

reviews.title: Cold food
reviews.text: Food was cold asparagus, second time the salmon was cold , for us no weather gets no value for money .has to pay a lot of money and then you get cold food

reviews.title: Bad experience during reception
reviews.text:
We had a reception after a family member burial service.  This was attended by other family members and friends. 
Two of my family members ended up in the ER units of ZGT and MST.  They had swallowed beef which was not cut into small pieces. 
My cousin ended up at ZGT in Hengelo and was released after they got the large piece of beef out of his throat. 
The other family member stayed for 9 days at MST after being re-animated at the restaurant after being in the ER for one day and then transfer to a recovery department at the same hospital. 
Maybe an idea to cut the beef in smaller portions and have a knife alongside the dish.

reviews.title: Bad experience at this restaurant
reviews.text: Good morning, we had a funeral for my mother here on April 16. We were served plates of steak without a knife. There were quite large chunks of meat in the plate. I choked on a large piece of meat that day, which left me in the hospital for 10 .days. A good tip for next time: give everyone a knife and cut the meat into smaller pieces and what I think is scandalous is that I have not heard any reaction from you. Kind regards Fons Huiskes

reviews.text: A class restaurant which KIR always was ensures good parking and there always was.  It's totally gone now. For me exit KIR.

reviews.title: Fantastic!
reviews.text: A fantastic experience! Never dined at KIR before and by chance on the opening night of the new section. A beautiful atmosphere with the wooden arches and decor. Fantastic service, very attentive and neat. The food was also fantastic. The meat was deliciously tender with tasty sauces. Appetizers and desserts were also delicious. Extra nice that the crème brulee was caramelized at the table. Really nothing more than praise for the beautiful atmosphere, the delicious food and the fantastic service! We'll be back!

reviews.title: Always a pleasant experience at Kir
reviews.text: KIR dinner x bar is open 7 days a week and it is always busy. The ambiance is atmospheric and informal. No stiff stuff. We once again enjoyed our visit. KIR has a varied menu, so everyone can find something delicious. Assertive young service makes the evening pleasant.

reviews.title: Disappointment
reviews.text: With high expectations we thought we would have a delicious dinner at Kir's; what a disappointment. Unfortunately, every course was disappointing and for that price that shouldn't happen. The courses went from tasteless to burnt, nothing tickled the palate and it was far from special. The service was young but did a good job. In terms of atmosphere within the restaurant, it felt more like an all you can eat wok restaurant than somewhere where you would happily throw away all your money. All in all, no, not recommended.

reviews.title: Great food!
reviews.text: It was a business dinner. Everything was very nice: atmosphere, service, food, welcoming, music. Truffle teriyaki is definitely must try! Coffee with a set of small sweets was delicious.

reviews.title: Expensive since rebranding.
reviews.text: This place must have changed owners or managers. They freshen up the place and changed the name, but your going to paying for it. Crap you now buy water by the 750 ml bottles. Our food for four people had be sitting till it was room temperature and none of it was done to order. Look it was Friday night and the place was busy but this establishment will be in trouble if can't straighten out the quality issues our dinner and drinks cost over 70 Euro's person and it was crap.

reviews.title: Consistently Good
reviews.text: I have been to this restaurant on several occassions by myself and with colleagues.  The food and drink are consistently good.  Nice looking restaurant and good service.

reviews.title: Nice menu get food
reviews.text: What an awesome place to while away an evening with friends. This place has a nice warm feel and is not overly noisy inspite of being busy. The service was great and the food was excellent from beef to Lamb to chicken and all things in between. I suspect this is not a place for a quick meal particular for dinner but it has a great unhurried atmosphere which lends itself to a nice time with friends and family.
